#why used to install SASS
# Ensure Node.js is Installed

  Verify Node.js is installed by running:

    **node -v **

    If not installed, download and install Node.js from https://nodejs.org/.

# Install SASS Using npm

    Open a terminal and run the following command to install SASS:

    npm install sass -v 3.7.4

# Verify Installation

  Confirm that SASS is installed by checking its version:

sass --version

Ensure the output matches the version you installed.